{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:1",
      "text": "After this Job opened his mouth and cursed the day of his birth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:2",
      "text": "And Job said:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:3",
      "text": "“Let the day perish wherein I was born, and the night which said, ‘A man-child is conceived.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:4",
      "text": "Let that day be darkness! May God above not seek it, nor light shine upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:5",
      "text": "Let gloom and deep darkness claim it. Let clouds dwell upon it; let the blackness of the day terrify it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:6",
      "text": "That night—let thick darkness seize it! let it not rejoice among the days of the year, let it not come into the number of the months.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:7",
      "text": "Yea, let that night be barren; let no joyful cry be heard in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:8",
      "text": "Let those curse it who curse the day, who are skilled to rouse up Leviathan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:9",
      "text": "Let the stars of its dawn be dark; let it hope for light, but have none, nor see the eyelids of the morning;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:10",
      "text": "because it did not shut the doors of my mother's womb, nor hide trouble from my eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:11",
      "text": "“Why did I not die at birth, come forth from the womb and expire?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:12",
      "text": "Why did the knees receive me? Or why the breasts, that I should suck?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:13",
      "text": "For then I should have lain down and been quiet; I should have slept; then I should have been at rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:14",
      "text": "with kings and counselors of the earth who rebuilt ruins for themselves,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:15",
      "text": "or with princes who had gold, who filled their houses with silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:16",
      "text": "Or why was I not as a hidden untimely birth, as infants that never see the light?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:17",
      "text": "There the wicked cease from troubling, and there the weary are at rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:18",
      "text": "There the prisoners are at ease together; they hear not the voice of the taskmaster.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:19",
      "text": "The small and the great are there, and the slave is free from his master.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:20",
      "text": "“Why is light given to him that is in misery, and life to the bitter in soul,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:21",
      "text": "who long for death, but it comes not, and dig for it more than for hid treasures;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:22",
      "text": "who rejoice exceedingly, and are glad, when they find the grave?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:23",
      "text": "Why is light given to a man whose way is hid, whom God has hedged in?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:24",
      "text": "For my sighing comes as my bread, and my groanings are poured out like water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:25",
      "text": "For the thing that I fear comes upon me, and what I dread befalls me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.3.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:26",
      "text": "I am not at ease, nor am I quiet; I have no rest; but trouble comes.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
